.TH PRINT 1 "2026" "The-JLC-Project" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
print \- print a string to stdout
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B print
.I string
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B print
writes
.I string
followed by a newline to standard output.
This is the JLC equivalent of
.BR echo (1).
No escape processing is performed; the string is printed literally.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Wrong number of arguments.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Print a message:
.EX
print "Hello, world"
.EE
.TP
Use in a script:
.EX
print "Build complete"
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR echo (1),
.BR printf (1)
.SH AUTHORS
The-JLC-Project contributors.
